article.headline: Louisiana Tech 59, McNeese State 50
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- Chad McKenzie and Marcus Elliott each scored 13 points to lead Louisiana Tech to a 59-50 victory over McNeese State on Wednesday. Tech (1-3) ran up an early lead and then held back a McNeese State challenge to get the win. The Bulldogs went out front by as many as 13 points in the first half and, by intermission, were up 27-21. In the second period, Tech had as much as a 17 point lead. But McNeese clawed its way back, primarily on shooting by Jarvis Bradley, who scored 15 to lead the Cowboys (1-4). Troy Aaron, the only other player in double figures for McNeese, added 10. Neither team had a hot hand from the floor. Louisiana Tech made 33.9 percent of its shots, compared to McNeese State's 31.4 percent. Tech held a 46-30 rebound edge over the Cowboys, with Harry Disy claiming a game-high 15. Bradley led McNeese with nine and was the game-leader in blocked shots with three.
